@baseUrl = http://localhost:5263
@token = Bearer techhive-secret-token
### Note: Change the port above to match your running application's port (e.g., 5000, 5153, etc.)


### ==========================================
### STANDARD CRUD OPERATIONS (Activity 1)
### ==========================================

### 1. GET All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Accept: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### 2. GET User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### 3. POST New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "Charlie Davis",
  "email": "charlie.davis@techhive.com",
  "department": "Engineering"
}

###

### 4. PUT Update User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "Alice Smith-Jones",
  "email": "alice.jones@techhive.com",
  "department": "HR Leadership"
}

###

### 5. DELETE User
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### 6. VERIFY Deletion (GET All Users again)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Accept: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

###


### ==========================================
### DEBUGGING & EDGE CASES (Activity 2)
### ==========================================

### 7. POST Validation Failure (Empty Name, Bad Email)
### Expected Result: 400 Bad Request with a list of validation errors.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "department": "Engineering"
}

###

### 8. GET Non-existent ID Retrieval
### Expected Result: 404 Not Found with message "User with ID 999 not found."
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/999
Accept: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### 9. POST Valid Creation (Optimized ID)
### Expected Result: 201 Created. ID should be generated instantly without iterating.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "David Miller",
  "email": "david.miller@techhive.com",
  "department": "Finance"
}

###


### ==========================================
### MIDDLEWARE TESTS (Activity 3)
### ==========================================

### 10. TEST AUTHENTICATION: Missing Token
### Expected Result: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Accept: application/json

###

### 11. TEST AUTHENTICATION: Invalid Token
### Expected Result: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer wrong-token-123

###

### 12. TEST ERROR HANDLING: Trigger Exception
### Expected Result: 500 Internal Server Error with { "error": "Internal server error." }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/trigger-error
Accept: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

### 13. TEST LOGGING: Check your terminal!
### After running any of the requests above, look at the terminal where `dotnet run` is executing.
### You should see logs like: "info: LoggingMiddleware[0] TechHive Audit Log - Method: GET, Path: /api/users, Status: 200"